e know today as »video«. This comprehensive theory of video entails a discussion of the technological, historical, and etymological roots, the media-theoretical concepts of medium and index, the philosophical and art-theoretical environment in which video emerged in the 1960s, the psychoanalytic concept of the phantasm, and artworks by artists such as Yael Bartana and Hito Steyerl.  afunded by Minerva Stiftung Gesellschaft für die Forschung mbH  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 4aAesthetics. 4aArt History. 4aArt. 4aFine Arts. 4aImage. 4aMedia Aesthetics. 4aMedia Art. 4aMedia. 4aPsychoanalysis. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aArt History.  aArt.  aFine Arts.  aImage.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Art.  aMedia.  aPsychoanalysis.2 aMinerva Stiftung Gesellschaft für die Forschung mbHefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z97831107685100 cprintz978383765700540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839457009?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839457009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839457009/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076851-0  transcript English Front